@startuml
title Diagrama de despliegue - TPScouting en Render

node "Usuario" {
  artifact "Navegador Web" as Browser
}

cloud "Render" {
  node "Web Service\nhttps://tpscouting-mvp.onrender.com" as RenderWeb {
    node "Gunicorn\n--workers 1 --threads 2" as Gunicorn {
      node "Flask App\nTPScouting" as FlaskApp {
        artifact "app.py" as AppPy
        folder "routes/" as Routes
        folder "templates/" as Templates
        folder "static/" as Static
        folder "ml/" as MLRuntime
        artifact "model.pt" as ModelPT
        artifact "preprocessor.joblib" as Preprocessor
        artifact "probability_calibrator.joblib" as Calibrator
      }
    }
  }

  database "PostgreSQL administrado\nBase demo" as RenderDB
}

node "Repositorio GitHub" as GitHub {
  artifact "Codigo fuente" as Code
  artifact "render.yaml" as RenderYaml
  artifact "requirements.txt" as Requirements
}

Browser --> RenderWeb : HTTPS
RenderWeb --> Gunicorn : Request HTTP interno
Gunicorn --> FlaskApp : WSGI
FlaskApp --> RenderDB : SQLAlchemy / psycopg
FlaskApp --> ModelPT : carga modelo
FlaskApp --> Preprocessor : carga preprocesador
FlaskApp --> Calibrator : carga calibrador

GitHub --> RenderWeb : Deploy desde rama main

note right of RenderDB
En produccion/demo no se usa SQLite
para evitar perdida por filesystem efimero.
end note

note bottom of Gunicorn
Configuracion documentada para MVP:
1 worker + 2 threads.
Los locks/cache son in-memory.
end note

@enduml
